      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Government Analytical Laboratory ¶ Melbourne ¶ Mar 31 1873 ¶ The Chief Inspector of Stock Melbourne ¶ Sir...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">73.03.31</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">William Johnson to John Kerr</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">D73/4020, unit 663, VPRS 3991 inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">Trans. Angela. To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Johnson died in 1887. M, who was identified as 'one of his few friends', contributed to his obituary in <seg style="font-style: italic; ">The chemist and druggist of Australasia</seg>, vol. ii, no. 5 (I May 1887), p. 135.</p>
               </note>Government Analytical Laboratory</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Mar 31 1873</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The Chief Inspector of Stock Melbourne</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have examined the contents of the stomach of a cow delivered to me by Mr. G. Mitchell and sent by you for analysis.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Amongst the vegetable product present I detected a number of seeds having the size and general shape and peculiar appearance of the seeds of nightshade depicted Page 359 Taylors Medical Jurisprudence with the same michroscopical s[…], I could not detect any of the structure of the plant the whole being too much masticated.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Treated chemically by Staas Procep the contents of the stomach yielded a bitter alkalard giving a yellow green state with chloride of […] and a brown one with Iodine solution - two tests pointing to […] same very allied salt (Solanin, Datur.) — the plant forwarded with the stomach Dr Mueller pronounces to be "Solanane Nigiun" — a well known poison plant - there can be no doubt this was the cause of death.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Wm Johnson</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Govt Analyst<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The letter has been countersigned by Graham Mitchell who forwarded it, with his own letter, to Kerr.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
